WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.600 align:middle line:90%


00:00:01.600 --> 00:00:02.400 align:middle line:90%
>> Hello.

00:00:02.400 --> 00:00:03.510 align:middle line:90%
I'm Georgia Shakti-Hill.

00:00:03.510 --> 00:00:06.180 align:middle line:84%
I want to welcome you
to "Living in Balance."

00:00:06.180 --> 00:00:08.580 align:middle line:84%
We are going to
take a journey home.

00:00:08.580 --> 00:00:11.340 align:middle line:84%
We are going to come
back to ourselves.

00:00:11.340 --> 00:00:14.550 align:middle line:84%
And in order to do that,
we have to really find out

00:00:14.550 --> 00:00:17.690 align:middle line:84%
how we can take care of
ourselves-- self-care,

00:00:17.690 --> 00:00:18.600 align:middle line:90%
soul care.

00:00:18.600 --> 00:00:20.318 align:middle line:90%
Come join us.

00:00:20.318 --> 00:00:23.811 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:23.811 --> 00:00:39.810 align:middle line:90%


00:00:39.810 --> 00:00:42.450 align:middle line:84%
Of all the roles that we play,
sometimes the most difficult

00:00:42.450 --> 00:00:44.610 align:middle line:90%
one is just being ourselves.

00:00:44.610 --> 00:00:47.350 align:middle line:84%
And we do have lots of roles
that we are playing out there

00:00:47.350 --> 00:00:48.150 align:middle line:90%
in the world.

00:00:48.150 --> 00:00:49.530 align:middle line:90%
Some are challenging.

00:00:49.530 --> 00:00:50.610 align:middle line:90%
Many are stressful.

00:00:50.610 --> 00:00:54.030 align:middle line:84%
But we really need to know who
we are and what our center is

00:00:54.030 --> 00:00:55.920 align:middle line:84%
and how we can
care for ourselves.

00:00:55.920 --> 00:00:58.210 align:middle line:84%
There are people who
can help us with that.

00:00:58.210 --> 00:01:00.330 align:middle line:84%
And we do have with
us today Holly Bruno.

00:01:00.330 --> 00:01:01.508 align:middle line:90%
And that is her mission.

00:01:01.508 --> 00:01:02.550 align:middle line:90%
So I want to welcome you.

00:01:02.550 --> 00:01:03.870 align:middle line:90%
>> Thanks, Georgia.

00:01:03.870 --> 00:01:06.780 align:middle line:84%
>> You have an incredibly
diverse background from this.

00:01:06.780 --> 00:01:09.150 align:middle line:84%
[LAUGHS] As we had
said in your bio,

00:01:09.150 --> 00:01:10.500 align:middle line:90%
you are a recovering attorney.

00:01:10.500 --> 00:01:11.300 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:01:11.300 --> 00:01:14.192 align:middle line:84%
>> OK, had been an assistant
state's attorney general

00:01:14.192 --> 00:01:15.150 align:middle line:90%
for the state of Maine.

00:01:15.150 --> 00:01:15.950 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:01:15.950 --> 00:01:20.010 align:middle line:84%
>> A law professor, and now
you are on your soul's journey.

00:01:20.010 --> 00:01:20.880 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:01:20.880 --> 00:01:21.680 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:01:21.680 --> 00:01:25.440 align:middle line:10%
Well, I'm glad that you referred
to me as a recovering attorney,

00:01:25.440 --> 00:01:26.880 align:middle line:10%
because part of
being an attorney

00:01:26.880 --> 00:01:29.835 align:middle line:10%
was living a life
that-- well, first off I

00:01:29.835 --> 00:01:31.710 align:middle line:10%
would have to apologize
for being an attorney

00:01:31.710 --> 00:01:34.020 align:middle line:10%
because of the
reputation we have.

00:01:34.020 --> 00:01:37.890 align:middle line:84%
But the truth is, I became an
attorney as many people become

00:01:37.890 --> 00:01:40.350 align:middle line:84%
accountants or they
become doctors or they

00:01:40.350 --> 00:01:44.100 align:middle line:84%
become teachers, because someone
else wanted them to do that.

00:01:44.100 --> 00:01:46.590 align:middle line:84%
And I set about
becoming an attorney

00:01:46.590 --> 00:01:48.840 align:middle line:84%
because it was a challenge
that women were not allowed

00:01:48.840 --> 00:01:49.882 align:middle line:90%
to take on at that point.

00:01:49.882 --> 00:01:51.970 align:middle line:90%
This was in 1973.

00:01:51.970 --> 00:01:53.490 align:middle line:84%
And I did it for
years and years.

00:01:53.490 --> 00:01:56.880 align:middle line:84%
But I was never at
home within myself.

00:01:56.880 --> 00:02:00.120 align:middle line:84%
I always felt as if
I'm working so hard,

00:02:00.120 --> 00:02:02.490 align:middle line:90%
but I don't really feel happy.

00:02:02.490 --> 00:02:04.480 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, it didn't
bring out your best.

00:02:04.480 --> 00:02:05.910 align:middle line:90%
It wasn't really the true you.

00:02:05.910 --> 00:02:06.710 align:middle line:90%
Is that it?

00:02:06.710 --> 00:02:09.862 align:middle line:84%
>> In fact, what it brought
out was my fierce ego.

00:02:09.862 --> 00:02:11.820 align:middle line:84%
I would get in there and
be a zealous advocate.

00:02:11.820 --> 00:02:13.630 align:middle line:10%
And there's nothing
wrong with that,

00:02:13.630 --> 00:02:18.060 align:middle line:10%
but I didn't ever feel like
I was at peace inside myself.

00:02:18.060 --> 00:02:20.560 align:middle line:10%
In fact, I felt as if I were
running away from myself.

00:02:20.560 --> 00:02:22.980 align:middle line:84%
And so what it took, Georgia,
was when I turned 40,

00:02:22.980 --> 00:02:25.060 align:middle line:84%
and I was doing all
of these things,

00:02:25.060 --> 00:02:27.960 align:middle line:84%
and I was just nonstop,
working 14-hour days

00:02:27.960 --> 00:02:29.520 align:middle line:84%
and raising two
children and trying

00:02:29.520 --> 00:02:33.690 align:middle line:84%
to do everything perfectly, I
got a lump in my left breast.

00:02:33.690 --> 00:02:35.790 align:middle line:10%
And at that point,
I really felt that I

00:02:35.790 --> 00:02:37.980 align:middle line:10%
was having someone
spiritually shaking me

00:02:37.980 --> 00:02:41.040 align:middle line:10%
by the shoulder saying,
whose life is this

00:02:41.040 --> 00:02:42.240 align:middle line:10%
that you want to lead?

00:02:42.240 --> 00:02:44.340 align:middle line:84%
And that was the beginning
of my journey home.

00:02:44.340 --> 00:02:47.430 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, you know we have found
over and over that people talk

00:02:47.430 --> 00:02:50.530 align:middle line:84%
with us about, it is
often a health issue,

00:02:50.530 --> 00:02:53.430 align:middle line:84%
a very serious health
issue, that totally gets

00:02:53.430 --> 00:02:55.650 align:middle line:84%
your attention because
it's very humbling.

00:02:55.650 --> 00:02:59.580 align:middle line:84%
It has to have priority, and
so it is life changing often.

00:02:59.580 --> 00:03:01.980 align:middle line:84%
So there is a lesson that
you then did receive.

00:03:01.980 --> 00:03:02.780 align:middle line:90%
That was the gift.

00:03:02.780 --> 00:03:03.210 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:03:03.210 --> 00:03:05.835 align:middle line:10%
And you know what I'm hoping for
now, in fact, I'm praying for,

00:03:05.835 --> 00:03:07.710 align:middle line:10%
is that I don't have to
go through that again

00:03:07.710 --> 00:03:08.630 align:middle line:10%
to keep learning.

00:03:08.630 --> 00:03:09.430 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:03:09.430 --> 00:03:11.800 align:middle line:84%
>> Oh, please, let
me have this lesson.

00:03:11.800 --> 00:03:13.230 align:middle line:90%
OK, yeah, OK.

00:03:13.230 --> 00:03:16.650 align:middle line:10%
>> In fact, now I'm much more
open to what that inner voice

00:03:16.650 --> 00:03:19.560 align:middle line:10%
is talking about so that when
there's something that I'm not

00:03:19.560 --> 00:03:22.120 align:middle line:10%
facing, there's something that
I'm resisting, in other words,

00:03:22.120 --> 00:03:24.240 align:middle line:10%
when I'm running away
from my own home,

00:03:24.240 --> 00:03:27.040 align:middle line:10%
that I can sit with
myself and say--

00:03:27.040 --> 00:03:29.253 align:middle line:10%
and I call myself
things like sweetie.

00:03:29.253 --> 00:03:31.920 align:middle line:84%
OK, sweetie, what is it that you
really don't want to face here?

00:03:31.920 --> 00:03:33.860 align:middle line:84%
What is it that's
difficult for you?

00:03:33.860 --> 00:03:36.490 align:middle line:84%
And to stay with that instead
of running away from that.

00:03:36.490 --> 00:03:38.830 align:middle line:84%
But the truth is, I
learned in my family,

00:03:38.830 --> 00:03:42.180 align:middle line:84%
I learned in law school,
I learned to basically

00:03:42.180 --> 00:03:45.370 align:middle line:84%
be running and keeping busy and
working and being a work addict

00:03:45.370 --> 00:03:46.170 align:middle line:90%
all the time.

00:03:46.170 --> 00:03:47.700 align:middle line:90%
And you know what's fascinating.

00:03:47.700 --> 00:03:50.050 align:middle line:84%
Work addiction is approved
of in our society.

00:03:50.050 --> 00:03:50.850 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, yes.

00:03:50.850 --> 00:03:53.010 align:middle line:84%
>> People say, oh, it's
wonderful that you work 14-hour

00:03:53.010 --> 00:03:53.810 align:middle line:90%
days.

00:03:53.810 --> 00:03:54.660 align:middle line:90%
Isn't she a saint?

00:03:54.660 --> 00:03:56.430 align:middle line:84%
However if I were a
drug addict, people

00:03:56.430 --> 00:03:58.020 align:middle line:90%
would say, oh, you poor thing.

00:03:58.020 --> 00:04:00.450 align:middle line:84%
But they're both addictions,
and addictions take us away

00:04:00.450 --> 00:04:01.290 align:middle line:90%
from home.

00:04:01.290 --> 00:04:04.740 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, as I read about you
and this idea that so many of us

00:04:04.740 --> 00:04:07.260 align:middle line:84%
work, work, work, I thought, I
have to talk with this woman.

00:04:07.260 --> 00:04:11.460 align:middle line:84%
Because so many people that I
know that are successful women,

00:04:11.460 --> 00:04:15.590 align:middle line:84%
it's so hard not to continue
that battle all the time,

00:04:15.590 --> 00:04:16.390 align:middle line:90%
the work ethic.

00:04:16.390 --> 00:04:19.050 align:middle line:84%
And it's so hard to
slow down, to stop.

00:04:19.050 --> 00:04:21.990 align:middle line:84%
So you're bringing a message
to us how we can do that?

00:04:21.990 --> 00:04:22.920 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:04:22.920 --> 00:04:24.990 align:middle line:84%
I'm in fact asking first,
Georgia, what is it

00:04:24.990 --> 00:04:26.740 align:middle line:90%
that I'm running away from?

00:04:26.740 --> 00:04:29.220 align:middle line:84%
Why is it that I'm
afraid to stop?

00:04:29.220 --> 00:04:30.720 align:middle line:84%
And I'll just say
that what happened

00:04:30.720 --> 00:04:32.640 align:middle line:84%
for me was I discovered
I was running away

00:04:32.640 --> 00:04:37.440 align:middle line:84%
from feeling that I wasn't
really worthwhile unless I made

00:04:37.440 --> 00:04:39.450 align:middle line:84%
a certain number
of accomplishments.

00:04:39.450 --> 00:04:41.010 align:middle line:84%
I was stacking my
accomplishments

00:04:41.010 --> 00:04:42.780 align:middle line:90%
like buckwheat pancakes.

00:04:42.780 --> 00:04:44.280 align:middle line:84%
And so you know
what happened when

00:04:44.280 --> 00:04:47.000 align:middle line:84%
I decided no longer to
be a practicing attorney

00:04:47.000 --> 00:04:48.300 align:middle line:90%
and I took some time off.

00:04:48.300 --> 00:04:50.670 align:middle line:84%
I'd go to a party or I'd
meet people and they'd say,

00:04:50.670 --> 00:04:52.590 align:middle line:90%
and what is it that you do?

00:04:52.590 --> 00:04:54.870 align:middle line:84%
And I would suffer
because I didn't have

00:04:54.870 --> 00:04:56.320 align:middle line:90%
that string of fancy titles--

00:04:56.320 --> 00:04:57.120 align:middle line:90%
>> That label.

00:04:57.120 --> 00:04:57.570 align:middle line:90%
>> --after my name.

00:04:57.570 --> 00:04:58.110 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, the role.

00:04:58.110 --> 00:04:59.350 align:middle line:84%
>> And then I would say
something like, well,

00:04:59.350 --> 00:05:01.433 align:middle line:84%
I'm really finding out
what I'm meant to be doing.

00:05:01.433 --> 00:05:03.740 align:middle line:84%
And then people would
walk away as if--

00:05:03.740 --> 00:05:04.800 align:middle line:90%
but you know what?

00:05:04.800 --> 00:05:06.900 align:middle line:84%
Now I'm very
comfortable just being

00:05:06.900 --> 00:05:10.140 align:middle line:84%
in the process of
fulfilling my mission, which

00:05:10.140 --> 00:05:13.880 align:middle line:84%
is to help everyone, myself
first, find the way back home.

00:05:13.880 --> 00:05:14.680 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:05:14.680 --> 00:05:16.790 align:middle line:84%
>> And that means not
running to work all the time.

00:05:16.790 --> 00:05:18.623 align:middle line:84%
Because when I did that,
I was running away.

00:05:18.623 --> 00:05:20.222 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, we do
have to slow down.

00:05:20.222 --> 00:05:21.930 align:middle line:84%
And like you said, it
may not be a lesson

00:05:21.930 --> 00:05:23.100 align:middle line:84%
that we can get
right the first time.

00:05:23.100 --> 00:05:23.810 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:05:23.810 --> 00:05:25.410 align:middle line:84%
>> We have to learn
it over and over.

00:05:25.410 --> 00:05:28.110 align:middle line:84%
You have a series
of recommendations

00:05:28.110 --> 00:05:29.382 align:middle line:90%
that you have made.

00:05:29.382 --> 00:05:30.840 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to
go through those

00:05:30.840 --> 00:05:33.990 align:middle line:84%
because I think these are
excellent lessons for people.

00:05:33.990 --> 00:05:36.480 align:middle line:84%
So I think our first
one is just say no.

00:05:36.480 --> 00:05:37.410 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:05:37.410 --> 00:05:38.910 align:middle line:84%
You know, it's
fascinating because I

00:05:38.910 --> 00:05:42.250 align:middle line:84%
think that came out of Nancy
Reagan's Just Say No to Drugs.

00:05:42.250 --> 00:05:45.187 align:middle line:84%
But in fact, those of
us, particularly women,

00:05:45.187 --> 00:05:46.770 align:middle line:84%
who feel like we
need to be everything

00:05:46.770 --> 00:05:50.550 align:middle line:84%
to everybody all the time have
lost the skill of saying no.

00:05:50.550 --> 00:05:53.310 align:middle line:84%
And we've been told and
taught that it's a negative

00:05:53.310 --> 00:05:54.820 align:middle line:90%
to set up a boundary.

00:05:54.820 --> 00:05:57.910 align:middle line:10%
But if I don't have a boundary,
I don't have an identity.

00:05:57.910 --> 00:06:00.970 align:middle line:84%
So in terms of just saying
no, when someone says to me,

00:06:00.970 --> 00:06:04.338 align:middle line:84%
oh, I'm sure you can handle
this, part of me wants to say,

00:06:04.338 --> 00:06:05.880 align:middle line:84%
oh, yes, I'll take
on one more thing.

00:06:05.880 --> 00:06:08.550 align:middle line:84%
But now at age 53,
I'm saying, thank you

00:06:08.550 --> 00:06:11.160 align:middle line:84%
for having the confidence
in me, and I'm not

00:06:11.160 --> 00:06:12.552 align:middle line:90%
going to do that right now.

00:06:12.552 --> 00:06:14.010 align:middle line:84%
>> When you say
set our boundaries,

00:06:14.010 --> 00:06:15.177 align:middle line:90%
that would be our guideline.

00:06:15.177 --> 00:06:16.470 align:middle line:90%
Now what is the boundary?

00:06:16.470 --> 00:06:18.630 align:middle line:84%
How do you know, when
is it time to say no?

00:06:18.630 --> 00:06:20.760 align:middle line:90%
When is it OK to say no?

00:06:20.760 --> 00:06:22.920 align:middle line:84%
Do you go to that
inner feeling about it?

00:06:22.920 --> 00:06:23.820 align:middle line:90%
Tell me about that.

00:06:23.820 --> 00:06:26.610 align:middle line:84%
>> I go to the inner feeling,
but it's almost as if I

00:06:26.610 --> 00:06:29.040 align:middle line:90%
envision a flow of a river.

00:06:29.040 --> 00:06:33.390 align:middle line:84%
And if the river keeps
flowing out to everybody else,

00:06:33.390 --> 00:06:35.250 align:middle line:84%
after a while, it
has no place else--

00:06:35.250 --> 00:06:36.810 align:middle line:90%
it's not coming from any source.

00:06:36.810 --> 00:06:38.020 align:middle line:90%
It can dry up.

00:06:38.020 --> 00:06:39.120 align:middle line:10%
You see what I'm saying?

00:06:39.120 --> 00:06:41.430 align:middle line:84%
But if I'm open to all of
these other streams coming

00:06:41.430 --> 00:06:44.890 align:middle line:84%
into the river, then
the river just flows.

00:06:44.890 --> 00:06:47.760 align:middle line:84%
So what I feel is I can
have the sense inside me

00:06:47.760 --> 00:06:51.030 align:middle line:84%
where I've gotten out of
touch with feeling peaceful,

00:06:51.030 --> 00:06:52.350 align:middle line:90%
with feeling happy.

00:06:52.350 --> 00:06:55.410 align:middle line:84%
I feel like some energy
beyond me is driving me.

00:06:55.410 --> 00:06:59.100 align:middle line:84%
And that's when I know,
that's not sacred energy.

00:06:59.100 --> 00:07:01.350 align:middle line:84%
That's just a work
addiction energy.

00:07:01.350 --> 00:07:03.030 align:middle line:90%
It's a different feeling.

00:07:03.030 --> 00:07:04.130 align:middle line:90%
>> So it is a feeling.

00:07:04.130 --> 00:07:05.520 align:middle line:90%
And I know I honor that feeling.

00:07:05.520 --> 00:07:09.112 align:middle line:84%
If I ask, do I want to do
this and I'm going to do this,

00:07:09.112 --> 00:07:11.070 align:middle line:84%
and how does the body
respond, and you actually

00:07:11.070 --> 00:07:13.020 align:middle line:84%
get a physical
reaction to something

00:07:13.020 --> 00:07:15.470 align:middle line:90%
you really don't want to do.

00:07:15.470 --> 00:07:16.270 align:middle line:90%
>> That's right.

00:07:16.270 --> 00:07:20.100 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, before I got
sick, I was so out of touch

00:07:20.100 --> 00:07:23.850 align:middle line:84%
with what my body was telling
me that I didn't pay attention.

00:07:23.850 --> 00:07:26.263 align:middle line:84%
But now I really am paying
much more attention.

00:07:26.263 --> 00:07:28.430 align:middle line:84%
There's so much wisdom in
my body to just listen to.

00:07:28.430 --> 00:07:28.785 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, it is.

00:07:28.785 --> 00:07:29.743 align:middle line:90%
>> Have you found that?

00:07:29.743 --> 00:07:30.990 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, yeah, absolutely.

00:07:30.990 --> 00:07:35.190 align:middle line:84%
Now the next point that you make
is distinguish between tasks.

00:07:35.190 --> 00:07:37.820 align:middle line:84%
Now what do you mean
by distinguishing?

00:07:37.820 --> 00:07:40.090 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, those of us who are
recovering perfectionists

00:07:40.090 --> 00:07:43.080 align:middle line:84%
and not just recovering
attorneys think that everything

00:07:43.080 --> 00:07:45.640 align:middle line:84%
we do has to be done perfectly,
including making my bed.

00:07:45.640 --> 00:07:46.440 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:07:46.440 --> 00:07:47.410 align:middle line:90%
>> So--

00:07:47.410 --> 00:07:49.710 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, I know this one, right?

00:07:49.710 --> 00:07:53.610 align:middle line:84%
>> So what I need to do is to
decide that I'm not going to do

00:07:53.610 --> 00:07:54.480 align:middle line:90%
everything well.

00:07:54.480 --> 00:07:56.563 align:middle line:84%
There are some things I'm
going to do well enough.

00:07:56.563 --> 00:07:58.170 align:middle line:90%
And my bed is like--

00:07:58.170 --> 00:08:01.200 align:middle line:90%
it's not perfect, but it's made.

00:08:01.200 --> 00:08:02.880 align:middle line:84%
And for years, I would
suffer, even just

00:08:02.880 --> 00:08:03.963 align:middle line:90%
doing something like that.

00:08:03.963 --> 00:08:06.600 align:middle line:10%
But what I find is
important is for me to say,

00:08:06.600 --> 00:08:10.110 align:middle line:10%
if I'm going to do one thing
today, what is that one

00:08:10.110 --> 00:08:11.700 align:middle line:10%
thing that matters most?

00:08:11.700 --> 00:08:13.098 align:middle line:90%
And to focus on that.

00:08:13.098 --> 00:08:15.640 align:middle line:84%
And then to say, I'm not going
to accomplish the whole thing.

00:08:15.640 --> 00:08:17.040 align:middle line:84%
I'm not going to write
an article in one day.

00:08:17.040 --> 00:08:18.780 align:middle line:84%
But I'm going to spend
an hour this morning.

00:08:18.780 --> 00:08:20.155 align:middle line:84%
And at the end of
that, I'm going

00:08:20.155 --> 00:08:21.450 align:middle line:90%
to stop no matter where I am.

00:08:21.450 --> 00:08:23.920 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, that's your point
too, to schedule finite time

00:08:23.920 --> 00:08:24.720 align:middle line:90%
for tasks.

00:08:24.720 --> 00:08:26.500 align:middle line:84%
That's another point
that you've made.

00:08:26.500 --> 00:08:29.850 align:middle line:84%
So you can take
all day doing this,

00:08:29.850 --> 00:08:31.710 align:middle line:90%
or you can allot one hour.

00:08:31.710 --> 00:08:32.530 align:middle line:90%
Is that the idea?

00:08:32.530 --> 00:08:33.330 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:08:33.330 --> 00:08:36.419 align:middle line:84%
Some of us are naturally
open ended, go with the flow,

00:08:36.419 --> 00:08:38.250 align:middle line:90%
don't like to be restricted.

00:08:38.250 --> 00:08:41.530 align:middle line:84%
And so it's almost like going
into the shadow part of myself,

00:08:41.530 --> 00:08:43.350 align:middle line:84%
the lesser-known part
of myself to do this.

00:08:43.350 --> 00:08:45.180 align:middle line:10%
