00:16:05.640 --> 00:16:06.790 align:middle line:90%
>> You know what they say?

00:16:06.790 --> 00:16:10.810 align:middle line:84%
They say, don't attempt to
help the person next to you

00:16:10.810 --> 00:16:13.450 align:middle line:84%
until you have the mask
securely on your own face.

00:16:13.450 --> 00:16:15.220 align:middle line:90%
>> That is profound.

00:16:15.220 --> 00:16:17.740 align:middle line:84%
>> Why do we need to
be reminded of that?

00:16:17.740 --> 00:16:19.600 align:middle line:84%
>> I want you to
remind us of this.

00:16:19.600 --> 00:16:22.600 align:middle line:84%
Celebrate the little
things, or celebrate

00:16:22.600 --> 00:16:23.950 align:middle line:90%
the tiny things in life.

00:16:23.950 --> 00:16:26.920 align:middle line:84%
Tell me what that philosophy is,
and what do you mean by that?

00:16:26.920 --> 00:16:27.910 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, that's so hard.

00:16:27.910 --> 00:16:31.030 align:middle line:84%
I think in terms of giving
and receiving of gifts,

00:16:31.030 --> 00:16:34.180 align:middle line:84%
it's so comfortable to
give to someone else,

00:16:34.180 --> 00:16:36.970 align:middle line:84%
and it's so uncomfortable
to take for myself.

00:16:36.970 --> 00:16:41.260 align:middle line:84%
That when I do something,
I need to honor that.

00:16:41.260 --> 00:16:42.410 align:middle line:90%
I need to celebrate that.

00:16:42.410 --> 00:16:45.880 align:middle line:10%
So even if it's just something
like buying myself flowers,

00:16:45.880 --> 00:16:47.340 align:middle line:10%
that is such a great thing.

00:16:47.340 --> 00:16:49.180 align:middle line:84%
And when I encourage
people to do this,

00:16:49.180 --> 00:16:51.880 align:middle line:84%
I just say, let's just make
a deal, just one little thing

00:16:51.880 --> 00:16:53.320 align:middle line:90%
you'll do for yourself.

00:16:53.320 --> 00:16:55.430 align:middle line:90%
The flurry of denial--

00:16:55.430 --> 00:16:56.230 align:middle line:90%
I can't do that.

00:16:56.230 --> 00:16:57.030 align:middle line:90%
I won't do that.

00:16:57.030 --> 00:16:58.270 align:middle line:90%
It's remarkable.

00:16:58.270 --> 00:17:00.610 align:middle line:84%
But it starts with just
one small celebration,

00:17:00.610 --> 00:17:02.590 align:middle line:90%
and it builds.

00:17:02.590 --> 00:17:06.609 align:middle line:84%
>> Now you have recommended
nine books that we could read.

00:17:06.609 --> 00:17:09.440 align:middle line:84%
And I ask if you would just give
us a little bit of information

00:17:09.440 --> 00:17:10.240 align:middle line:90%
about them.

00:17:10.240 --> 00:17:12.910 align:middle line:84%
Now the first three that
we're going to take a look at,

00:17:12.910 --> 00:17:15.579 align:middle line:90%
why have you chosen these?

00:17:15.579 --> 00:17:18.260 align:middle line:84%
"Addicted to Perfection," and
you can see it on the monitor

00:17:18.260 --> 00:17:19.060 align:middle line:90%
there.

00:17:19.060 --> 00:17:23.680 align:middle line:84%
Why would you recommend
that particular book?

00:17:23.680 --> 00:17:27.550 align:middle line:10%
>> "Addicted to Perfection" is
very powerful because it talks

00:17:27.550 --> 00:17:31.870 align:middle line:10%
about the conditioning that
women in particular have

00:17:31.870 --> 00:17:35.500 align:middle line:10%
to lose respect for ourselves
and lose touch with our own

00:17:35.500 --> 00:17:40.540 align:middle line:10%
voice and to identify instead
with the good, the nice--

00:17:40.540 --> 00:17:42.630 align:middle line:10%
it sounds like a soap opera--

00:17:42.630 --> 00:17:44.230 align:middle line:10%
the good person
we're supposed to be,

00:17:44.230 --> 00:17:46.930 align:middle line:10%
the nice person, the perfect
person we're supposed to be.

00:17:46.930 --> 00:17:49.840 align:middle line:10%
And it's very difficult
because it essentially

00:17:49.840 --> 00:17:54.250 align:middle line:10%
says that I disenfranchise
myself from my source of power

00:17:54.250 --> 00:17:55.655 align:middle line:10%
by trying to be perfect.

00:17:55.655 --> 00:17:57.280 align:middle line:84%
>> And you mentioned
that word perfect,

00:17:57.280 --> 00:17:58.570 align:middle line:90%
and that's that key word.

00:17:58.570 --> 00:18:01.143 align:middle line:84%
We're used to making the
bed perfectly or doing this

00:18:01.143 --> 00:18:02.560 align:middle line:84%
perfectly, and
that's where you've

00:18:02.560 --> 00:18:05.440 align:middle line:84%
said, again, to forgive
ourselves a little bit.

00:18:05.440 --> 00:18:07.840 align:middle line:84%
>> On "Dancing on My Grave,"
now tell me about that,

00:18:07.840 --> 00:18:08.770 align:middle line:90%
the message in that.

00:18:08.770 --> 00:18:10.780 align:middle line:90%
>> That is so powerful.

00:18:10.780 --> 00:18:15.310 align:middle line:84%
A number of us as women
have eating disorders.

00:18:15.310 --> 00:18:18.760 align:middle line:84%
And that was written by a person
with an eating disorder who

00:18:18.760 --> 00:18:21.100 align:middle line:84%
felt that to be
the best ballerina,

00:18:21.100 --> 00:18:23.050 align:middle line:90%
she had to stop eating.

00:18:23.050 --> 00:18:26.080 align:middle line:84%
She had to deny
her own sustenance

00:18:26.080 --> 00:18:28.150 align:middle line:90%
to be perfect as a dancer.

00:18:28.150 --> 00:18:31.600 align:middle line:84%
>> And when we look at that, we
really have to love ourselves

00:18:31.600 --> 00:18:33.610 align:middle line:84%
and love ourselves as
we are, love our body.

00:18:33.610 --> 00:18:37.312 align:middle line:84%
And we really have to get
past that outside approval

00:18:37.312 --> 00:18:38.770 align:middle line:84%
of ourselves with
eating disorders.

00:18:38.770 --> 00:18:43.800 align:middle line:84%
>> Listen, I need to because
my natural body is not

00:18:43.800 --> 00:18:44.920 align:middle line:90%
a toothpick.

00:18:44.920 --> 00:18:45.840 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:18:45.840 --> 00:18:48.690 align:middle line:84%
I don't think it ever was,
except maybe when I was five.

00:18:48.690 --> 00:18:52.380 align:middle line:84%
And this sad thing that
we have this image of not

00:18:52.380 --> 00:18:54.120 align:middle line:84%
being beautiful
just as we are is

00:18:54.120 --> 00:18:55.370 align:middle line:90%
something I work on every day.

00:18:55.370 --> 00:18:58.140 align:middle line:84%
But to have a dancer
who didn't feel she

00:18:58.140 --> 00:19:01.120 align:middle line:84%
could be accepted unless
she was so svelte.

00:19:01.120 --> 00:19:01.920 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:19:01.920 --> 00:19:04.800 align:middle line:84%
>> And that is now, people are
really working on this to allow

00:19:04.800 --> 00:19:06.465 align:middle line:84%
for dancers to be
all different shapes.

00:19:06.465 --> 00:19:08.190 align:middle line:90%
But it's a steady, slow process.

00:19:08.190 --> 00:19:09.570 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, it is.

00:19:09.570 --> 00:19:11.370 align:middle line:84%
The third book
that you recommend

00:19:11.370 --> 00:19:12.630 align:middle line:90%
is "A History of God."

00:19:12.630 --> 00:19:13.880 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, now that's wonderful.

00:19:13.880 --> 00:19:14.680 align:middle line:90%
Aren't we all?

00:19:14.680 --> 00:19:17.730 align:middle line:84%
I mean, at the bottom of all of
this, of your work, of my work,

00:19:17.730 --> 00:19:23.230 align:middle line:84%
is the question, who is God,
and who does God want me to be?

00:19:23.230 --> 00:19:26.170 align:middle line:84%
And when I talk about God, I'm
open to anyone's view of God

00:19:26.170 --> 00:19:29.420 align:middle line:90%
or the universe or whatever.

00:19:29.420 --> 00:19:31.930 align:middle line:10%
But this book goes
through the history

00:19:31.930 --> 00:19:35.440 align:middle line:10%
of how people have seen God
and then allows each one of us

00:19:35.440 --> 00:19:38.230 align:middle line:10%
to say, all right, so
someone in a desert society

00:19:38.230 --> 00:19:41.830 align:middle line:10%
saw God living in a
wonderful, lush jungle.

00:19:41.830 --> 00:19:45.220 align:middle line:10%
What kind of desert am I in,
and what do I see God as,

00:19:45.220 --> 00:19:47.290 align:middle line:10%
and what is God truly to me?

00:19:47.290 --> 00:19:50.655 align:middle line:84%
>> In the next little series
of books that you recommended,

00:19:50.655 --> 00:19:52.530 align:middle line:84%
"Do What You Love and
the Money Will Follow."

00:19:52.530 --> 00:19:53.330 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:19:53.330 --> 00:19:55.150 align:middle line:84%
>> Isn't that a
wonderful affirmation?

00:19:55.150 --> 00:19:56.600 align:middle line:90%
I love that.

00:19:56.600 --> 00:19:58.510 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's sort
of self-explanatory.

00:19:58.510 --> 00:20:01.368 align:middle line:84%
But what about
"Facing Codependency"?

00:20:01.368 --> 00:20:03.160 align:middle line:84%
That's still an issue
with a lot of people.

00:20:03.160 --> 00:20:06.040 align:middle line:84%
We've been working on that
as a society collectively,

00:20:06.040 --> 00:20:08.590 align:middle line:84%
and that codependency is
really out there, is it not?

00:20:08.590 --> 00:20:11.200 align:middle line:84%
>> Codependency means that
I'm out of touch with who I am

00:20:11.200 --> 00:20:13.030 align:middle line:84%
because I'm so involved
in meeting someone

00:20:13.030 --> 00:20:14.560 align:middle line:90%
else's expectations.

00:20:14.560 --> 00:20:15.782 align:middle line:90%
I meet that every day.

00:20:15.782 --> 00:20:16.990 align:middle line:90%
>> And it isn't psychobabble.

00:20:16.990 --> 00:20:17.800 align:middle line:90%
It's reality.

00:20:17.800 --> 00:20:19.270 align:middle line:90%
And it's ruining people's lives.

00:20:19.270 --> 00:20:22.140 align:middle line:84%
>> For me, it's
absolute reality.

00:20:22.140 --> 00:20:23.860 align:middle line:84%
The Stone Center at
Wellesley College

00:20:23.860 --> 00:20:25.420 align:middle line:84%
has a piece of
information I find

00:20:25.420 --> 00:20:29.140 align:middle line:84%
fascinating that says that
girls, when we're born,

00:20:29.140 --> 00:20:31.810 align:middle line:84%
learn as much about how
to take care of our moms

00:20:31.810 --> 00:20:35.270 align:middle line:84%
as our moms are
teaching us how to--

00:20:35.270 --> 00:20:36.070 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:20:36.070 --> 00:20:39.280 align:middle line:84%
>> Basically we're focusing on
our mom and giving care as well

00:20:39.280 --> 00:20:40.270 align:middle line:90%
as taking care.

00:20:40.270 --> 00:20:42.940 align:middle line:84%
>> And who is the perfect
woman, by the way--

00:20:42.940 --> 00:20:44.120 align:middle line:90%
the book?

00:20:44.120 --> 00:20:44.920 align:middle line:90%
>> That's right.

00:20:44.920 --> 00:20:45.880 align:middle line:90%
I have not met her.

00:20:45.880 --> 00:20:47.185 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:20:47.185 --> 00:20:49.230 align:middle line:84%
>> Or are you looking
at her in the mirror?

00:20:49.230 --> 00:20:50.030 align:middle line:90%
>> You know what?

00:20:50.030 --> 00:20:53.295 align:middle line:84%
I think all of us is
exactly perfect as we are.

00:20:53.295 --> 00:20:54.670 align:middle line:10%
And that's Pia
Mellody, who wrote

00:20:54.670 --> 00:20:57.550 align:middle line:10%
that book says that we need
to befriend our perfectly

00:20:57.550 --> 00:20:59.080 align:middle line:10%
imperfect natures.

00:20:59.080 --> 00:21:00.670 align:middle line:90%
>> Ah, I like that.

00:21:00.670 --> 00:21:03.670 align:middle line:84%
Now in the last group, you
have "Reinventing Work."

00:21:03.670 --> 00:21:06.160 align:middle line:84%
And how do we need to look
at our work differently?

00:21:06.160 --> 00:21:10.300 align:middle line:84%
>> Matthew Fox, wonderful
writer and speaker,

00:21:10.300 --> 00:21:16.030 align:middle line:84%
says that work and spirituality
have been separated off so that

00:21:16.030 --> 00:21:20.900 align:middle line:84%
work is just producing money,
or work is just a livelihood.

00:21:20.900 --> 00:21:23.840 align:middle line:10%
But work today needs
to have meaning.

00:21:23.840 --> 00:21:25.570 align:middle line:10%
And a lot of what
I do is to invite

00:21:25.570 --> 00:21:28.540 align:middle line:10%
people to find-- re-find, again,
the meaning in their work.

00:21:28.540 --> 00:21:31.820 align:middle line:84%
Because if my work
is fulfilling,

00:21:31.820 --> 00:21:33.110 align:middle line:90%
it's spiritually fulfilling.

00:21:33.110 --> 00:21:34.770 align:middle line:84%
It's not just
bringing home money.

00:21:34.770 --> 00:21:34.990 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:21:34.990 --> 00:21:37.490 align:middle line:84%
>> And people burn out unless
they have that spiritual base.

00:21:37.490 --> 00:21:39.580 align:middle line:84%
So what Matthew Fox
is saying is it's

00:21:39.580 --> 00:21:42.190 align:middle line:90%
OK to do work that's spiritual.

00:21:42.190 --> 00:21:43.570 align:middle line:90%
It's very much like--

00:21:43.570 --> 00:21:46.990 align:middle line:90%
what's our friend from PBS?

00:21:46.990 --> 00:21:48.590 align:middle line:84%
The man who said
do what you love.

00:21:48.590 --> 00:21:49.390 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, yes.

00:21:49.390 --> 00:21:50.320 align:middle line:90%
>> Joseph Campbell.

00:21:50.320 --> 00:21:50.830 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, I love Joseph.

00:21:50.830 --> 00:21:51.670 align:middle line:90%
>> Do what you love.

00:21:51.670 --> 00:21:54.170 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I am so pleased that
you have been sharing with us.

00:21:54.170 --> 00:21:56.140 align:middle line:84%
And we'll just mention
your last two, "Zen

00:21:56.140 --> 00:21:58.720 align:middle line:84%
and the Art of Making a Living"
and "Work with Passion."

00:21:58.720 --> 00:22:01.330 align:middle line:84%
But we really are, in this
bottom line, what you're

00:22:01.330 --> 00:22:03.490 align:middle line:90%
saying, self care, soul care.

00:22:03.490 --> 00:22:05.530 align:middle line:90%
Come back to who you are.

00:22:05.530 --> 00:22:06.410 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:22:06.410 --> 00:22:08.230 align:middle line:84%
The thing is,
there's never going

00:22:08.230 --> 00:22:10.360 align:middle line:84%
to be another one of
you or me, so why not

00:22:10.360 --> 00:22:11.965 align:middle line:90%
accept it and enjoy it?

00:22:11.965 --> 00:22:14.410 align:middle line:84%
>> The beautiful, perfect
women that we are.

00:22:14.410 --> 00:22:15.280 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:22:15.280 --> 00:22:16.990 align:middle line:84%
>> And each of
you out there too.

00:22:16.990 --> 00:22:19.060 align:middle line:84%
That is the exciting
part, that you really

00:22:19.060 --> 00:22:20.320 align:middle line:90%
need to love yourself.

00:22:20.320 --> 00:22:21.820 align:middle line:84%
What we're going
to do is let you

00:22:21.820 --> 00:22:25.060 align:middle line:84%
know how you can be in touch
with Holly Bruno for self care

00:22:25.060 --> 00:22:27.397 align:middle line:90%
and soul care.

00:22:27.397 --> 00:22:30.820 align:middle line:90%
